2. ATM Booth Access
Only one person can use an ATM booth at a time. Two people approach the booth.
If the booth is occupied, the other must wait.

Create an ATMBooth class with synchronized methods using wait() and notify().

Threads represent Person A and Person B, printing:

Person A started using ATM…
Person B waiting for ATM…
Person A done…
Person B started using ATM…
Person B done…
3.Print Queue with One Printer

There is only one printer available in an office. Two employees try to print documents.
If the printer is busy, the other must wait.

Create a Printer class that tracks whether the printer is busy.
Use wait() and notify() to coordinate the two print jobs.

Threads should output something like:

Employee 1 started printing…
Employee 2 waiting for printer…
Employee 1 finished printing…
Employee 2 started printing…
Employee 2 finished printing…

4.Single Charging Station
A charging station has only one charging port. Two electric bikes arrive to charge.

Implement a ChargingStation class with wait()/notify() for synchronization.

Threads represent Bike A and Bike B with messages like:

Bike A started charging…
Bike B waiting for its turn…
Bike A finished charging…
Bike B started charging…
Bike B finished charging…

